Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:06.895 --> 00:00:09.000
Four Seasons Pizza

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:11.500
Makes: 4 medium pizza

00:00:11.500 --> 00:00:13.500
Ingredients for the dough

00:00:13.500 --> 00:00:17.800
500 g (3½ cups) bread flour

00:00:17.800 --> 00:00:20.000
½ tbsp salt

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:22.000
½ tsp sugar

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:25.000
2 tbsp olive oil

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:28.000
2 tsp active dried yeast

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
250 ml (1 cup) lukewarm water

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:33.500
Ingredients for the sauce

00:00:33.500 --> 00:00:36.000
500 g grated fresh tomatoes

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:39.000
2½ tbsp olive oil

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:42.000
2 tsp tomato paste

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:44.000
1 garlic clove, crushed

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.000
6 basil leaves or 1 tsp dried basil

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:50.500
1/3 tsp dried oregano

00:00:50.500 --> 00:00:53.000
1/3 tsp white pepper

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:55.500
1/3 tsp salt

00:00:55.500 --> 00:00:57.000
Ingredients for the topping

00:00:57.000 --> 00:01:01.000
220g (2 cups) grated mozzarella cheese

00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:03.000
2 tbsp olive oil

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:12.000
8 tbsp chopped green bell pepper

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:18.000
8 tbsp chopped red bell pepper

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:22.000
12 white mushroom, sliced

00:01:22.000 --> 00:01:26.000
8 tbsp sliced black olives

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:28.000
1 tsp dried oregano

00:01:28.500 --> 00:01:31.000
Directions for the dough

00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:40.500
Sift the flour and salt in a large bowl, mix and make a well in the center.

00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:48.000
In a jug whisk the water with the yeast, sugar and olive oil 

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:54.000
and let it rest for 10 minutes until the top gets foamy.

00:01:54.000 --> 00:02:09.500
then pour the mixture into the well and gradually mix the flour into the liquid until fully combined.

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:15.500
With you hand bring the dough together until it forms a ball.

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:29.000
Transfer to a work surface and knead until smooth. The dough is ready when you press with your fingers and it goes back to its shape.

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:32.000
Brush the dough with olive oil

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:44.000
and place it into a large bowl, cover with plastic wrap and let it rest in a warm place for about 1 hour until doubled in size.

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:50.000
Transfer the dough to a work surface and knead it briefly to release the air.

00:02:50.500 --> 00:03:01.000
The dough is now ready to use or it can be wrapped in plastic and stored in the fridge for 3 days or frozen.

00:03:01.000 --> 00:03:02.500
Directions for the sauce

00:03:02.500 --> 00:03:08.000
Wrap basil leaves together with a string.

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:14.000
Heat the olive oil in a pot and sauté the garlic.

00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:23.000
Add the tomato paste, oregano and pepper and stir well.

00:03:23.000 --> 00:03:28.500
Add the grated tomatoes and salt and stir well.

00:03:28.500 --> 00:03:36.500
Then add the basil leaves and leave the sauce simmering over low heat for 1 hour, stirring from time to time.

00:03:36.500 --> 00:03:44.000
Discard the basil leaves and mix the sauce in a mixer until smooth.

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:46.000
To finish the pizza

00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:50.000
Brush a large round baking tray with olive oil

00:03:50.000 --> 00:03:59.000
Dust your work surface with a little flour, cut the dough in four and roll out each piece in a circle shape 

00:03:59.000 --> 00:04:11.000
Place the dough into the baking tray, pressing the borders gently.

00:04:11.000 --> 00:04:18.000
Prick the dough with a knife then spread 2 tbsp of tomato sauce.

00:04:18.000 --> 00:04:23.000
and sprinkle the 1/4 of the grated mozzarella cheese.

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:35.000
Scatter 1/4 of the diced red pepper, green pepper, diced tomatoes, olives and mushrooms on top.

00:04:35.000 --> 00:04:40.000
Sprinkle some dried oregano on top and drizzle 1 tbsp of olive oil.

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:46.000
Cover with plastic wrap and chill in the fridge for 30 minutes.

00:04:46.000 --> 00:04:55.000
Repeat the same process with the remaining dough and ingredients to make 4 pizza.

00:04:55.000 --> 00:05:05.000
Remove the plastic wrap and bake the pizza in a preheated oven at 180°C. for 12 minutes.

